# BDD Guardian

## Architecture

- `src/core/` — framework-agnostic (index, parsing, matching). No VS Code API here.
- `src/providers/` — per-framework binding detection and parsing.
- `src/features/` — VS Code UI (CodeLens, hover, diagnostics, Coach, navigation).

See `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` for data flow. Do not edit compiled output in `out/`.

## Before finishing a change

- Run `npm test` from the repo root (includes compile + lint).
- Changes in `src/core/` or matching behavior: add or update Vitest tests under `src/__tests__/`.
- User-visible strings: update `src/i18n/en.json` and `src/i18n/es.json`.

## Binding matching (invariants)

- Single matching path: regex via `compileBindingRegex` in `src/core/parsing/bindingRegex.ts`.
- Do not add a resolver fallback that matches literal step text against all bindings unless explicitly requested.
- Step and pattern whitespace: same normalization (see `docs/BINDING_MATCHING.md`).
- For matching work, prefer the `@bdd-binding-matcher` skill.

## Providers and Coach

- New framework: follow `docs/PROVIDERS.md` and register in `src/providers/bindings/providerManager.ts`.
- New Coach rule: mirror `src/features/coach/rules/` and wire in `rules/index.ts` with tests in `coach.test.ts`.
